      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EXPENSIVE ICON (4) gets the nod in another ordinary maiden. Did a good job to finish third over 1000m here on debut then a bottomless track brought him undone last start. Good enough to turn things around and take this out. Short-priced favourite BE SOMEONE (1) wasn't the best away but gathered momentum late to get up for third on debut over 1000m here 16 days ago. Should take a lot from that experience and is better placed out to this trip. CANNYSTEP (2) last appeared when down the track on debut over 1300m at Kembla in February. This is many lengths weaker so don't write him off. MACAU PRINCE (6) made progress last start when lining up for the second time. Can play a role here if he continues that trajectory. SUNNY QUARTERS (9) hasn't been all that far away in her two runs to date. In the mix with the aid of the inside draw.",
